I have more developments of my web comic that I want to share/get input on.
So, I guess if you want to listen and and give input Dadro I will welcome it but what I will talk about will kinda build off of what I have discussed before with Bgr and others.

I got to thinking about the opening of my comic and how best to go about doing it. We discussed last time how having the first page or two be images of the scene, in this a case a futuristic cityscape, to set up the universe for the reader.
Sure, if I see something I can have an opinion on. But I'm kind of here and not. Watching a Sound Design panel demo from Mick Gordon on another tab

I thought a great way to incorporate that with my story is to have these first two pages kinda follow the two main characters doing stuff in the city. Like, they will look just like other people in the city but if you pay attention you will notice them.
But these scenes will show a good portion of the scenery and the tone of the universe.

As for editing, good luck mate. I took three years of audio editing in college to get my engineer certification, there's a whole lot to learn about editing SFX. Just try to get your hands on recordings that won't require you to do something silly like
Whisper Fail and Dadrobit. Name a more iconic duo.
Yay, I have roughly planned out around the first 25 pages of my comic!
That page list is growing right now so...I predict future writers block when I need more pages.

Here is an interesting idea. So last time it seemed like a good idea to end the first chapter of my comic right at the bombshell moment. But that is way far out. So, what if I split the comic up into two types of sections: books and chapters?

A book would be a collection of chapters. So, the end of book 1 will be at the bombshell moment but the first chapter will end on day on of my comic as, now that I have it planned out, works out well as it is a bit of an introduction.
Reread what is my Chapter 1 and I like it. I think the whole book/chapter system will work well.
I suppose it is time to give Twokinds another read. Especially with all these ideas floating around in my head. Bye everyone!
